Package com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters

The com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters package provides interfaces to manage desired state configuration and software for a cluster of ESX hosts.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Configuration
    The Configuration interface provides methods to manage desired configuration of an ESX cluster.
    ConfigurationTypes
    The Configuration interface provides methods to manage desired configuration of an ESX cluster.
    DepotOverrides
    The DepotOverrides interface provides methods to manage software depots overriden for a given cluster.
    DepotOverridesTypes
    The DepotOverrides interface provides methods to manage software depots overriden for a given cluster.
    InstalledImages
    The InstalledImages interface provides methods to examine the software bundle running on group of ESXi hosts in a cluster.
    InstalledImagesTypes
    The InstalledImages interface provides methods to examine the software bundle running on group of ESXi hosts in a cluster.
    Software
    The Software interface provides methods to manage desired software specification of an ESX cluster.
    SoftwareTypes
    The Software interface provides methods to manage desired software specification of an ESX cluster.

Package com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters Description

The com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters package provides interfaces to manage desired state configuration and software for a cluster of ESX hosts.
